Question 1
A group of people who not only interact with each other but also similar characteristics
and a sense of unity can be referred to as a social group. The three social groups I associate
myself with include family, peer group such as millennial, and community such as Africa-
American.
The family is the first group that an individual gets to know first. A family is the main
social network in the life of any individual or gathering of people. It is from this that an
individual appends and comprehends the estimations of culture, absorbs the main social jobs and
gains the experience of social conduct. In the family, this individual makes their first strides,
encounters the first delights and distresses, and afterward, leaves the family and faces a major
world. The individual will then return if things get tough out there. The family is an intricate
social formation. Every individual from the family is both a special distinction and an essential
piece of an entire family gathering. The family is a small social group.
A peer group is a group of individuals from around a similar age, societal position, and
interests. By and large, individuals are generally equivalent regarding power when they
cooperate with friends. In the case of Millennial, it comprises of a group of people born between
the early 1980s to early 2000s.
A community is a group of individuals with shared characteristic and shared traits. Apart
from living in the same place, people in a given community feel they belong to each other and

care about each other. Being an African-American makes me an associate and a group member
of the African-American community.
The song I would pick is Kendrick Lamar’s ‘Alright.’ This song is among the many songs in
Lamar’s 2015 album “To Pimp a Butterfly.” The song is a mix of hip-hop jazz and a myriad of
other music genres. 2016 single ‘Alright’ has become the anthem of the generation. The song
comforts the people of color as well as other oppressed communities. The song gives me hope
and a feeling that despite tensions growing worse and worse everything and everyone will be
alright.
The artist I could pick to make a chart-topping hit with is Pharrell Williams. For instance,
liberation has been a dream for most African-American communities. Picking Pharrell would see
to it that the social and political themes of liberation are put across as he has done in his previous
hit songs including ‘Freedom.’
Question 2
Eminem’s ‘Till I Collapse’ single is my favorite song when I need a little motivation to
get up and start running. In the year 2017, the song was the most downloaded workout song as
reported by music streaming service Spotify. Typically, music goes hand in hand with exercise.
When working out, listening to music will keep you working out for long hours, harder, and even
brighten one's mood in the process. Listening to Eminem’s ‘Till I Collapse’ song keeps one
moving. The song uplifts an individual’s spirit and keeps one moving longer and stronger.
Replacing ‘Till I Collapse’ as my workout song would be difficult considering that my body and
mind is already tuned to the song. The tune of the song tunes my body ready for a workout. ‘Till
I Collapse’ is people’s choice and getting it out of the way would take years.

Question 3
My favorite YouTube videos include “heal the world by Michael Jackson” and “where
do broken hearts go by Whitney Houston”. These two videos generally summarize the two sides
of my life, how I relate with myself and my interactions. Watching these two videos remind me
of a couple of memories that will last forever. In ‘heal the world’, the lyrics and the footage of
kids playing remind me of my childhood days where I hardly had any worries about tomorrow.
The next video is about the lyrics that remind me of some breakdown I had over some
relationship. These music videos show the sentimental part of my life that has remained
exclusively to me.
These two music videos have shared the artistic value and carry a strong message of love
to the community and to spouses. The teachings that music videos help to push through the
actions can help in several ways. Music videos are essential in creating awareness, warning and
educating. However, there are others that are just made for entertainment purposes.
I engage people with music videos online and offline. I like understanding the different
perspectives that come with the opinions of others about the same. Online, I engage them
through comments and posts that create an interactive session. Offline, I ask random questions
about new and old music videos.
Question 4
Music is an essential art when I seek to relax my mind in a soothing manner. There exist
different kinds of music which fit my every kind of mood, for example, happy, sad, annoyed or

afraid to approach or do something. Some of these types of music include soul music, country
music, and Rnbs. Music helps to bring out the emotions I have. Continuous developments in
technology have impacted the music sector. Through improved technology, music recording is
made simpler. Currently, music is found in almost all internet platforms, for example, YouTube
and Facebook. Moreover, music helps in the spread of innovative strategies and ideas on the
music is able to reach a wide range of people in the communities. I feel that music motivates me

music, I would find it difficult to deal with emotions and also carry out some physical activities,
for example, house chores and also some exercises in the gym.
I cannot operate a vinyl. Vinyl is a tool that holds music in its hard form. With the
emergence of new technology, all the music is now contained in the compact disk which is easily
movable making it possible to listen to different kind of music anywhere. Therefore a vinyl is
mostly viewed as an old fashioned tool no longer needed as much. Moreover, there are no
efforts to bring the vinyl back in use since most of the citizens are more than satisfied with the
digital tools.
